  <summary date="2020-08-04T16:46:11Z" status="Introduced in House">Schools Preventing Hunger in At-Risk Kids Act or the SPARK ActThis bill expands automatic eligibility for the National School Lunch Program to foster children who have been placed with a relative or family friend&#160;with the involvement of&#160;the state child welfare agency. To enroll in the program, a family must document the foster child's status to the child's school.</summary>
